#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:305
msgid "2. Feeding Doxygen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:307
msgid ""
"Not all headers files are collected automatically. You have to add the "
"desired C/C++ header paths within the sub-config files of Doxygen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:310
msgid ""
"Sub-config files have the unique name ``.doxyfile``, which you can usually "
"find near directories that contain documented headers. You need to create a "
"new config file if there's not one located in a path close(2-depth) to the "
"headers you want to add."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:314
msgid ""
"Sub-config files can accept any of Doxygen_ `configuration options <https://"
"www.doxygen.nl/manual/config.html>`__, but do not override or re-initialize "
"any configuration option, rather only use the concatenation operator \"+=\". "
"For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:318
msgid ""
"# to specify certain headers\n"
"INPUT += @CUR_DIR/header1.h \\\n"
"         @CUR_DIR/header2.h\n"
"# to add all headers in certain path\n"
"INPUT += @CUR_DIR/to/headers\n"
"# to define certain macros\n"
"PREDEFINED += C_MACRO(X)=X\n"
"# to enable certain branches\n"
"PREDEFINED += NPY_HAVE_FEATURE \\\n"
"              NPY_HAVE_FEATURE2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:330
msgid ""
"@CUR_DIR is a template constant returns the current dir path of the sub-"
"config file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:334
msgid "3. Inclusion directives"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:336
msgid ""
"Breathe_ provides a wide range of custom directives to allow converting the "
"documents generated by Doxygen_ into reST files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:340
msgid ""
"For more information, please check out \"`Directives & Config Variables "
"<https://breathe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/directives.html>`__\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:343
msgid "Common directives:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:345
msgid "``doxygenfunction``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:347
msgid ""
"This directive generates the appropriate output for a single function. The "
"function name is required to be unique in the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:350
msgid ""
".. doxygenfunction:: <function name>\n"
"    :outline:\n"
"    :no-link:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:356
msgid ""
"Checkout the `example <https://breathe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/function."
"html#function-example>`__ to see it in action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:360
msgid "``doxygenclass``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:362
msgid ""
"This directive generates the appropriate output for a single class. It takes "
"the standard project, path, outline and no-link options and additionally the "
"members, protected-members, private-members, undoc-members, membergroups and "
"members-only options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:367
msgid ""
".. doxygenclass:: <class name>\n"
"   :members: [...]\n"
"   :protected-members:\n"
"   :private-members:\n"
"   :undoc-members:\n"
"   :membergroups: ...\n"
"   :members-only:\n"
"   :outline:\n"
"   :no-link:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:379
msgid ""
"Checkout the `doxygenclass documentation <https://breathe.readthedocs.io/en/"
"latest/class.html#class-example>`__ for more details and to see it in action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:382
msgid "``doxygennamespace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:384
msgid ""
"This directive generates the appropriate output for the contents of a "
"namespace. It takes the standard project, path, outline and no-link options "
"and additionally the content-only, members, protected-members, private-"
"members and undoc-members options. To reference a nested namespace, the full "
"namespaced path must be provided, e.g. foo::bar for the bar namespace inside "
"the foo namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:390
msgid ""
".. doxygennamespace:: <namespace>\n"
"   :content-only:\n"
"   :outline:\n"
"   :members:\n"
"   :protected-members:\n"
"   :private-members:\n"
"   :undoc-members:\n"
"   :no-link:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:401
msgid ""
"Checkout the `doxygennamespace documentation <https://breathe.readthedocs.io/"
"en/latest/namespace.html#namespace-example>`__ for more details and to see "
"it in action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:404
msgid "``doxygengroup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:406
msgid ""
"This directive generates the appropriate output for the contents of a "
"doxygen group. A doxygen group can be declared with specific doxygen markup "
"in the source comments as covered in the doxygen `grouping documentation "
"<https://www.doxygen.nl/manual/grouping.html>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:410
msgid ""
"It takes the standard project, path, outline and no-link options and "
"additionally the content-only, members, protected-members, private-members "
"and undoc-members options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:413
msgid ""
".. doxygengroup:: <group name>\n"
"   :content-only:\n"
"   :outline:\n"
"   :members:\n"
"   :protected-members:\n"
"   :private-members:\n"
"   :undoc-members:\n"
"   :no-link:\n"
"   :inner:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:425
msgid ""
"Checkout the `doxygengroup documentation <https://breathe.readthedocs.io/en/"
"latest/group.html#group-example>`__ for more details and to see it in action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:433
msgid "Legacy directive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:435
msgid ""
"If a function, module or API is in *legacy* mode, meaning that it is kept "
"around for backwards compatibility reasons, but is not recommended to use in "
"new code, you can use the ``.. legacy::`` directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:439
msgid ""
"By default, if used with no arguments, the legacy directive will generate "
"the following output:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:-1
msgid "Legacy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/howto-docs.rst:443
msgid ""
"This submodule is considered legacy and will no longer receive updates. This "
